-- Development Bank of Southern Africa Says Profit Falls 56% to $82 Million
-- Ana Monteiro
-- 2010-06-25T06:05:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/development-bank-of-southern-africa-says-profit-falls-56-to-82-million.html

          
          
             Development Bank of Southern Africa
Ltd., a state-owned lender, said profit for the year through
March declined 56 percent.  
 Net income retreated to 622.3 million rand from 1.43
billion rand a year earlier, the company said in a statement
published in Johannesburg-based Business Day newspaper today.  
 Net interest income retreated 7.1 percent to 1.63 billion
rand, it said.  
 Loans and equity disbursements fell 11 percent to 8.26
billion rand, while total assets increased 12 percent to 45.1
billion rand.  
 South Africa’s finance ministry agreed to a guarantee of
15.2 billion rand to support creditors while an increase in the
lender’s callable capital to 20 billion rand from 4.8 billion
rand is approved by parliament, the bank said.  
